## 🌐 The TCP/IP Model (4 Layers) — The Practical Workhorse

What actually runs the internet. Consolidates OSI layers into fewer, practical groupings.

| TCP/IP Layer | Maps to OSI Layers | Responsibility | Protocols |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Application** | 5, 6, 7 (Session, Presentation, Application) | User-facing services + session mgmt | HTTP, FTP, SMTP, DNS, Telnet, SSH |
| **Transport** | 4 (Transport) | Host-to-host transfer | TCP, UDP |
| **Internet** | 3 (Network) | Logical addressing, routing | IP, ICMP, ARP |
| **Network Access** | 1, 2 (Physical, Data Link) | Physical transmission, hardware addressing | Ethernet, Wi-Fi, PPP |

