## ⚠️ Common Mistakes

- **Forcing a strict 1:1 OSI ↔ TCP/IP mapping** — TCP/IP consolidates layers; it's not perfectly symmetric.
- **Troubleshooting only at the Application layer** — always start low (cable/physical → IP → DNS) and work up.
- **Assuming port numbers are global** — ports are per-host, used to distinguish services on that host only.
- **Forcing every protocol into one OSI layer** — some protocols (e.g. TLS) span layers depending on context.

