## 🛡️ Defensive Engineering Notes

| Layer Concept | Defensive Action |
|---|---|
| Firewalls inspect IP (L3) + ports (L4); WAFs inspect app traffic (L7) | Configure firewalls to block all unneeded ports/protocols; allow only essentials (e.g. 80/443 for a web server) |
| Insecure protocols (Telnet, FTP, HTTP) | Replace with secure equivalents: SSH, SFTP/FTPS, HTTPS |
| Network segmentation via IP subnetting (L3) | Use VLANs (L2) + subnetting to isolate sensitive systems |
| IDS/IPS inspect multiple layers | Deploy IDS/IPS that analyze Network, Transport, and Application layer traffic |

