## 📝 Chapter Summary

- OSI (7 layers) = theoretical/educational framework for dissecting network functions
- TCP/IP (4 layers) = practical model that actually runs the internet
- Encapsulation/decapsulation = how data is packaged going down the stack and unpacked coming up
- `ping` and `netstat` = simple tools to observe Network Layer and Transport Layer behavior respectively
- Layer knowledge directly informs firewall rules, protocol security choices, segmentation, and IDS/IPS design

